  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n$ npx hardhat --version\r\n2.10.0\r\n\r\n### Version of Forge\r\n$ forge --version\r\nforge 0.2.0 (388c3c0 2023-04-10T09:31:50.093051900Z)\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nHello,\r\n\r\nI am trying to install hardhat-foundry. \r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nI have already [installed build sources from Foundry following the next guide for Windows](https://getfoundry.sh/). However, when I try to install Foundry NPM package from hardhat using the next command:\r\n\r\n`npm i @nomicfoundation/hardhat-foundry`\r\n\r\nI get the next output:\r\n\r\n``` bash\r\n# npm resolution error report\r\n\r\nWhile resolving: reinvestor@1.0.0\r\nFound: hardhat@2.10.0\r\nnode_modules/hardhat\r\n  dev hardhat@\"2.10.0\" from the root project\r\n\r\nCould not resolve dependency:\r\npeer hardhat@\"^2.12.6\" from @nomicfoundation/hardhat-foundry@1.0.1\r\nnode_modules/@nomicfoundation/hardhat-foundry\r\n  @nomicfoundation/hardhat-foundry@\"*\" from the root project\r\n\r\nFix the upstream dependency conflict, or retry\r\nthis command with --force or --legacy-peer-deps\r\nto accept an incorrect (and potentially broken) dependency resolution.\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\nhardhat, foundry, testing",
